OL,4,C'Mum's poems taught us not to fear
OL,5,Cdeath'
OL,6, When poet Helen Dunmore was nearing the
OL,7, final stages of cancer, she told her
OL,8, daughter Tess Charnley one day:
OL,9, "Darling, check your email. There's
OL,10, something for you."
OL,12,F"And she'd emailed us all this final
OL,13,Fpoem, Hold Out Your Arms, about her
OL,14,Fimpending dying," Tess explained on BBC
OL,15,FRadio 4's Today programme on Wednesday.
OL,17,FHold Out Your Arms was written on 25
OL,18,FMay 2017. Dunmore died less than two
OL,19,Fweeks later at the age of 64.
